Remarks: Nipponnemertes ganahai resembles N. africana (Wheeler, 1940), N. danae (Friedrich, 1957) (probably synonym of N. pulchra in morphological basis; Berg, 1985), N. magna (Punnett, 1903), N. pulchra (Johnston, 1837), and N. sanguinea Riser, 1998 in having pale pink to yellow body (
Figures 6A–E
